title: Faroe Islands Food Inflation
description: Cost of food in Faroe Islands increased 9.90 percent in September of 2022 over the same month in the previous year. Food Inflation in Faroe Islands averaged 1.56 percent from 2002 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 9.90 percent in the third quarter of 2022 and a record low of -1.60 percent in the fourth quarter of 2009. This page provides - Faroe Islands Food Inflation- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: Statistics Faroe Islands
